cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI

The paper focuses on improving the data efficiency of neural networks through the use of novel implementations of activation functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents results for image classification (MNIST and CIFAR-10) and vector classification (DementiaBank), indicating that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of interpolation and extrapolation techniques in the activation functions suggests that the paper may also belong to the Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
